# User Data Deletion Policy for Genesis Journey

**Effective date:** March 16, 2026

This User Data Deletion Policy explains how players of **Genesis Journey** may delete data associated with their use of the game.

## 1. Overview

Genesis Journey is designed to minimize personal data collection. In its current form, most game data, if any, is stored locally on the user’s device to support gameplay features such as saved progress, settings, and preferences.

Depending on the version of the game, users may request deletion of certain data as described below.

## 2. Types of Data That May Be Deleted

The following types of data may be eligible for deletion:

- Local saved game progress
- Settings and gameplay preferences
- Character selections or journey progress
- Support messages voluntarily sent to us
- Account-related data, if accounts or cloud save features are added in the future

## 3. How to Delete Local Game Data

If Genesis Journey stores gameplay data only on your device, you may delete that data by:

- Uninstalling the app from your device
- Clearing the app’s local storage through your device settings, where available

Deleting the app or clearing local storage may permanently remove your saved progress, preferences, and related game data stored on that device.

## 4. How to Request Deletion of Support or Contact Data

If you previously contacted us by email or another support channel and want that information deleted, you may submit a deletion request using the contact details below.

Please include enough information for us to locate your message, such as:

- Your email address used to contact us
- The approximate date of your message
- A brief description of your request

## 5. How to Request Deletion of Account Data

If a future version of Genesis Journey includes user accounts, cloud saves, or online profiles, users may request deletion of their account and associated data by contacting us or by using any in-app deletion feature made available.

Where required, deletion of an account will remove the account from our active records, along with associated personal data that we are not legally required or otherwise permitted to retain.

## 6. Verification of Requests

To protect user privacy and security, we may take reasonable steps to verify that a deletion request is made by the correct person before processing the request.

## 7. Retention Exceptions

We may retain limited information when necessary to:

- Comply with legal obligations
- Resolve disputes
- Enforce agreements
- Protect the security, integrity, and operation of the game
- Maintain basic business or tax records where required by law

If retention is required for legal or operational reasons, we will delete the data when retention is no longer necessary or permitted.

## 8. Processing Time

We will make reasonable efforts to process valid deletion requests within a reasonable timeframe, subject to the nature of the data and any legal obligations.

If additional time is needed, we may notify the requester where appropriate.

## 9. Third-Party Services

If Genesis Journey uses third-party platforms or services, such as app stores, analytics providers, crash reporting tools, or cloud services, data held by those services may also be subject to their own deletion processes and privacy policies.

Users may need to review the policies of those third parties for additional information.

